    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term used during the mid-18th century for armchairs with upholstered seats and backs, carved frames and cabriole legs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
